name: Luca Solórzano
child_characteristics:
Agreeableness: Is compassionate, has a soft heart, Is respectful, treats others with respect, Has a forgiving nature, Assumes the best about people, Is polite, courteous to others
Conscientiousness: Is systematic, likes to keep things in order, Is dependable, steady, Is reliable, can always be counted on, Tends to be disorganized, Can be somewhat careless, Sometimes behaves irresponsibly
Extraversion: Is outgoing, sociable, Is talkative, Is full of energy, Shows a lot of enthusiasm, Is sometimes shy, introverted
Neuroticism (Emotional Stability): Worries a lot, Is temperamental, gets emotional easily, Stays optimistic after experiencing a setback
Openness to Experience: Is curious about many different things, Is complex, a deep thinker, Is inventive, finds clever ways to do things, Is original, comes up with new ideas, Values art and beauty

Additional characteristics:
He is bilingual and in a dual-immersion program, where he speaks Spanish and English. He strongly values Hispanic culture and does Baile Folklórico. He is an active child who loves baseball and wrestling. He enjoys running and is competitive. He is the oldest of three kids.
parenting_style: Firm parenting boundaries with a gentle parenting approach. Multicultural household. Values honesty, education, and always putting in the best effort. Teamwork and cooperation are important as we learn emotional regulation and respect for others.
